column3: “I got a nicely grown strain of Tiger Woods; thick dense buds almost kushy style.  I am very picky and kept puffing it down until the girlfriend snagged it from my resiny lips.  Again, my strain was grown well so it taste nice before lighting up and even better afterwards.  I am impressed and would like to sample it again from different places to really compare the grows.  I read the other reviews and my guess is that...”
“pretty decent hybrid, nothing special. sells for pretty cheap, good value.”
“Luckily this stuff was grown very nicely! Will update after we burn some if we don't end up golfing.”
“Great strain for all-day smoking.  Opened up the bag and smelled Lipton iced tea. Trichomes are barely turning amber brown - aged, cured well.”
“Pretty nice strain. Has a really vibrant fresh out of the pack" sweet smell to it. Doesn't get you wild high. It def produces a really nice
column6: "easy to zone out" kind of buzz. Would def recommend this to someone needin a slight pick-up but also in search of the giggles. Can def have you overthinkin things if not careful as the high creeps up after 15/20 minutes.”"

column3: “Forsure good starter strain, good for experienced people too..really nice hybrid helps a lot with nausea and has a good baseline high that will put you in a uplifted good mood that will leave you smiling the whole high”
“Very good smell, reminds me of a tea smell. Taste great.”
